"title": "8481: self-sacrifice",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8481",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The willingness to leave one's possessions or to give them to others; to deny oneself to the point of death or to give oneself in the service of God or other people.</p>\n<h2>Self-sacrifice as forfeiting one's present comfort for the sake of others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:11\">RUT 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:33-Gen44:34\">GEN 44:33–44:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:34\">HEB 10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:24-Heb11:27\">HEB 11:24–11:27</a></p>\n<h2>Self-sacrifice as giving one's possessions to others</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ commends the willingness to give away one's possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:33\">LUK 12:33</a></p>\n<h3>God rewards those who give their possessions away</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:28-Luke18:30\">LUK 18:28–18:30</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:27-Matt19:29\">MAT 19:27–19:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:28-Mark10:30\">MRK 10:28–10:30</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrificing one's possessions as demonstrated in the life of the church</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:44-Acts2:45\">ACT 2:44–2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:32-Acts4:37\">ACT 4:32–4:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:1-2Cor8:5\">2CO 8:1–8:5</a></p>\n<h2>Self-sacrifice as leaving all and following Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Such sacrifice is a condition of discipleship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:33\">LUK 14:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:37\">MAT 10:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:26\">LUK 14:26</a> <em>This means loving Jesus Christ over and above one's immediate family.</em></p>\n<h3>Those willing to leave everything to follow Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:27-Luke5:28\">LUK 5:27–5:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8\">PHP 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Self-sacrifice as the metaphorical laying down of one's life for others</h2>\n<h3>Followers of Jesus Christ are required to give themselves in the service of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:24-John12:25\">JHN 12:24–12:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:38\">MAT 10:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:27\">LUK 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24-Matt16:25\">MAT 16:24–16:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34-Mark8:35\">MRK 8:34–8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23-Luke9:24\">LUK 9:23–9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:33\">LUK 17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:16-1John3:18\">1JN 3:16–3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those who demonstrated such self-sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:10-2Cor4:11\">2CO 4:10–4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19-1Cor9:23\">1CO 9:19–9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:30-1Cor15:31\">1CO 15:30–15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:23-2Cor11:29\">2CO 11:23–11:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:15\">2CO 12:15</a></p>\n<h2>Self-sacrifice as the literal laying down of one's life</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ warns his disciples to be prepared to give their lives</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:21-Matt10:22\">MAT 10:21–10:22</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12-Mark13:13\">MRK 13:12–13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:16-Luke21:17\">LUK 21:16–21:17</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrificing one's life is of no value without love</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:3\">1CO 13:3</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those willing to give their lives for the sake of God and others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:23-Acts20:24\">ACT 20:23–20:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:32\">EXO 32:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:15-1Chr11:19\">1CH 11:15–11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:14-Esth4:16\">EST 4:14–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:35-Mark14:36\">MRK 14:35–14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:17\">PHP 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those who gave their lives in God's service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:36-Judg11:38\">JDG 11:36–11:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:5–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:36-Heb11:38\">HEB 11:36–11:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a></p>",
